<div class="sec" style="background:var(--c-band);border-top:1px solid var(--c-band-border);border-bottom:1px solid var(--c-band-border)">
  <p class="eyebrow">The problem</p>
  <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:820px">
    Most teams have world-class science or world-class engineering — rarely both, and almost
    never with the regulatory fluency that clinical-grade software demands.
  </h2>
  <p class="body" style="max-width:720px">
    That gap is where good digital health companies quietly fail. Bridging from scientific idea
    to an investable product concept with a robust regulatory and technology strategy is
    intrinsically complex, and an easy place to stall without expert insight.
  </p>
